TY  - JOUR
AB  - The equilibrium allocation of capital and equilibrium market prices are derived for a world economy with unified securities market, mobile capital, no uncertainty, and varying tax rates on different sources of income in each country. The paper then characterizes optimal tax rates for a small country in this setting, focusing on the peculiar incentives created when the before-tax rate of return differs among securities due to differences in their typical tax treatment.
